# CI Guardrails and Ratchets

- Treat file-size guardrail failures as refactor triggers, not bypass prompts.
- Keep workflow trigger paths minimal and intentional.
- Update validation scripts when behavior changes introduce new invariants.

## Ratchet Discipline

- If hot files exceed cap, extract modules before merging.
- Prefer small, behavior-preserving refactors to keep CI green.
- Any exception entry should include rationale and expiry.

## Verification

- Run `python3 scripts/check_file_sizes.py`.
- Confirm relevant workflow still triggers for changed paths.
- Re-run targeted validators tied to changed subsystem(s).
